<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[102138]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The Altars Route pays tribute to the dead]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>All Saints Day.</strong> The Mexican community celebrates All Saints Day by building traditional altars to pay homage to the dead.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The Altars Route will be held in Barcelona for the 8th year running on All Saints Day. This festivity is deeply rooted in Mexican culture, and the Mexicans celebrate it with music, flowers, dances and offerings to remember their dead and keep their memories alive.</p>
<p>Altars are part of a millenary Mexican tradition. It is usual to put out dishes and drinks of all kinds to welcome the dead with the things they most enjoyed in life. There are also objects related to the person receiving the homage. Twenty establishments are participating in the initiative In Barcelona.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
